On Mon, 5 Feb 2007, Tim Frank wrote:

> Have I read this correctly?  As it stands, removing the wire from the
> sender does not make the light go
> out.  Does this mean that I have a short in the wiring from the idiot
> light??  Or is there any other
> explanation??

Sounds like you have a short somewhere.  The oil light works by grounding
the circuit at the engine, so you have a short somewhere between the light
and the engine.

George
